On Motion of the State, the Court amends Count #1 to a Misdemeanor Battery, domestic abuse, a Class A misdemeanor, contrary to 940.19(1) & 968.075(1)(a)

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Counts #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #1 & #2, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 18 months, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail (on Ct#1), with Huber/Work-release privileges; to commence 12/27/14 by 7:00 pm 
--To undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--Cooperate will all treatment & counseling programs
--To maintain employment
--No acts/threats of violence
--No contact with Vicente Rosales Solis except as incidental for employment purposes
--To pay restitution of $2992.93 payable to Vicente Rosales Solis - Court notes that ability for Defendant to pay that amt. while on probation is questionable. If she can not pay within the period of probation, such failure, assuming it is not willful, shall not be the cause of any revocation or extension, but should then be entered into a civil judgment.
--To pay $299.29 restitution processing fee - Court notes that ability for Defendant to pay that amt. while on probation is questionable. If she can not pay within the period of probation, such failure, assuming it is not willful, shall not be the cause of any revocation or extension, but should then be entered into a civil judgment.
--To pay costs of $486 ($243 each count)
--To pay $400 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)
--To pay $200 domestic abuse surcharge ($100 each count)
